            </li>
            <li>
              <p>It is solely your responsibility to choose a signing method that is suitable for the given legal act and complies with applicable legal requirements. If you are unsure, we recommend using a qualified electronic signature or seeking legal advice.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>The visual representation of a signature inserted into a document may have only informational or usability meaning. The legal binding effect of an electronic signature is determined by the technical and cryptographic data contained in or associated with the document, not by the visual representation of the signature itself.</p>
            </li>
          </ol>
